  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nAll received mentions are counted as new by the unread message counter, even if they were read.\r\nIn other words, if the user receives a mention, opens the chat to read it, returns to the home screen, and receives another mention, the count `2` will be shown, although only one mention was received. \r\nAlso, all mention messages are displayed as new after relogin.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nRefresh the unread message counter when reading a mention message; display `1` when one new mention is received. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/141995204-499be66a-0c63-4251-9408-d3fb0101df01.MP4\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. UserA and UserB join the same public chat (works for any type of chat)\r\n2. UserA sends a message and returns to the home screen\r\n3. UserB sends a message mentioning UserA\r\n4. UserA opens the public chat and returns to the home screen\r\n5. UserB sends another mention of UserA\r\n6. UserA checks the unread counter on the public chat\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 16/11\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
